    {
      "name": "Sichuan Bang Bang Ji (Bang Bang Chicken)",
      "instructions": [
        "Poach the chicken breasts in boiling water with a few slices of ginger and a splash of Shaoxing wine for 12-15 minutes until fully cooked. Let cool.",
        "While cooling, prepare the sauce: whisk the peanut butter, Chinese sesame paste, light soy sauce, Chinkiang vinegar, sugar, minced garlic, minced ginger, and Sichuan chili oil together in a bowl until smooth. Thin with a tablespoon of warm water if too thick.",
        "Shred the cooled chicken breasts by hand into thin strips or tap them gently with a rolling pin to loosen the fibers first.",
        "Finely slice the spring onions.",
        "Arrange the shredded chicken on a serving plate, pour the savory, sweet, and nutty sauce over it, and garnish generously with the sliced spring onions and toasted sesame seeds."
      ],
      "required_ingredients": [
