        "Ginger",
        "Toasted Sesame Seeds"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Cong You Ji (Cantonese Scallion Oil Chicken)",
      "instructions": [
        "Gently poach the chicken breasts in a pot of water with sliced ginger and Shaoxing wine for 15 minutes. Submerge in ice water immediately to stop cooking, then drain and cut into bite-sized slices.",
        "Finely mince the spring onions (both green and white parts) and grate the ginger.",
        "Place the spring onions, ginger, and salt in a heatproof bowl.",
        "Heat the cooking oil in a small saucepan until it is smoking hot. Carefully pour the hot oil over the spring onion mixture; it should sizzle intensely and release a sweet, savory aroma.",
        "Stir a pinch of sugar and the light soy sauce into the scallion oil mixture.",
        "Drizzle the hot scallion oil sauce over the sliced chicken breasts and serve cold or at room temperature."
      ],
      "required_ingredients": [
