      "name": "Tomato and Egg Drop Soup (番茄蛋花汤)",
      "instructions": [
        "Beat the eggs lightly in a small bowl and set aside.",
        "In a pot, heat a tiny splash of vegetable oil over medium heat. Add the halved cherry tomatoes and stir-fry for 2 minutes until they begin to break down and release their color.",
        "Pour in 750ml of water and bring to a boil. Lower the heat to a simmer, then add the chicken bouillon powder, salt, and white pepper powder.",
        "Stir the cornstarch slurry (cornstarch mixed with 1 tbsp water) into the simmering soup to give it a very light body.",
        "Turn the heat down to low. Stir the soup slowly in one direction to create a gentle whirlpool, then slowly drizzle in the beaten eggs in a thin stream. Let the egg ribbons set for 10 seconds before stirring.",
        "Turn off the heat immediately. Stir in the sesame oil and garnish with chopped scallions."
      ],
      "required_ingredients": [
        {
          "name": "large free range eggs",
          "amount": "2"
