    {
      "name": "Tomato Egg Comfort Noodles (番茄鸡蛋面)",
      "instructions": [
        "Cook the wheat noodles in a pot of boiling water according to package instructions. Drain and transfer to a serving bowl.",
        "Whisk the eggs with a pinch of salt. Heat 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil in a wok, scramble the eggs until just cooked, and set aside.",
        "Heat another half tablespoon of oil in the wok. Sauté the minced garlic and scallion whites until aromatic.",
        "Add the cherry tomatoes, stir-frying until they break down completely into a rich, pulpy sauce. Add light soy sauce, oyster sauce, sugar, and salt.",
        "Pour in about 50ml of water to create a luscious gravy, and simmer for 1 minute.",
        "Return the scrambled eggs to the wok and mix well with the tomato sauce.",
        "Pour the hot tomato and egg mixture directly over the cooked noodles. Garnish with chopped scallion greens and serve immediately."
      ],
