    {
      "name": "Mao's Hunan Red Braised Pork",
      "instructions": [
        "Cut the pork belly into 2cm cubes.",
        "Blanch the pork belly cubes in boiling water with a slice of ginger for 3-4 minutes, then drain and rinse.",
        "Heat a tablespoon of cooking oil in a wok, add rock sugar, and cook on low heat until it melts and turns into an amber-colored caramel.",
        "Add the pork belly to the wok and stir quickly to coat all pieces with the caramelized sugar.",
        "Add sliced ginger, garlic cloves, star anise, and dried red chilies, stirring to release the aromatics.",
        "Pour in Shaoxing rice wine, light soy sauce, and dark soy sauce, then add enough hot water to just cover the pork.",
        "Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low, cover with a lid, and simmer for 50 minutes until the pork is tender.",
