        "Cut the pork belly into 3cm cubes.",
        "Blanch the pork belly in boiling water with a few slices of ginger for 5 minutes, then drain.",
        "In a dry wok over medium-low heat, sear the pork belly pieces until they start to brown and release their natural fats. Remove excess fat from the wok.",
        "Push the pork to the side, add the rock sugar and a splash of water, stirring on low heat until it dissolves and turns a light brown caramel.",
