      "instructions": [
        "Cut the pork belly into large 5cm square pieces.",
        "Blanch the pork pieces in boiling water for 5 minutes, then rinse thoroughly in cold water.",
        "In a heavy clay pot or Dutch oven, lay a thick, flat bed of whole scallions and sliced ginger at the bottom to prevent the pork from sticking.",
        "Place the pork belly squares skin-side down onto the scallions and ginger.",
        "Pour in the Shaoxing rice wine, light soy sauce, dark soy sauce, and rock sugar. Do not add any water; the liquid should come from the wine and sauces.",
        "Bring to a boil, cover with a tight-fitting lid, and simmer on the absolute lowest heat setting for 90 minutes.",
